I'll get another job.

985
00:39:49,196 --> 00:39:54,034
But because I was
and still am truly sorry.

986
00:39:56,120 --> 00:39:57,871
If I'd have let you on that plane,

987
00:39:57,955 --> 00:39:59,247
you would've brought Susie,

988
00:39:59,331 --> 00:40:01,708
and she would've tried to
stab me with a cheese knife.

989
00:40:01,792 --> 00:40:03,710
And I would have thrown
myself in front of you

990
00:40:03,794 --> 00:40:05,295
and taken the blow.

991
00:40:05,379 --> 00:40:06,880
And some Brie.

992
00:40:08,298 --> 00:40:09,883
Well…

993
00:40:11,885 --> 00:40:13,887
I sure have missed that brisket.

994
00:40:16,306 --> 00:40:18,475
I'll send Monica the recipe.

995
00:40:22,312 --> 00:40:25,440
You know, I'm back in the States

996
00:40:25,524 --> 00:40:27,192
for a while again next month.

997
00:40:27,276 --> 00:40:28,735
Cut another Christmas album.

998
00:40:28,819 --> 00:40:31,738
Hmm.
I know what to get my mother for Hanukkah.

999
00:40:31,822 --> 00:40:34,282
Maybe we could, uh, get together,

1000
00:40:34,366 --> 00:40:37,077
have a drink. I… I could take you to…

1001
00:40:37,161 --> 00:40:38,620
-No.
-No?

1002
00:40:38,704 --> 00:40:40,580
I'm not falling for that again.

1003
00:40:40,664 --> 00:40:42,624
We're not friends.

1004
00:40:42,708 --> 00:40:44,710
I have learned my lesson.

1005
00:40:48,714 --> 00:40:50,924
Congratulations.

1006
00:40:51,008 --> 00:40:56,847
I hope you're gonna be very happy…
Dwayne.

1007
00:41:05,273 --> 00:41:06,774
That's what I'm saying.

1008
00:41:06,858 --> 00:41:09,068
-Can we get out of here?
-Yeah, sure.

1009
00:41:09,152 --> 00:41:11,070
Bye. Thanks for the croutons.

1010
00:41:11,154 --> 00:41:13,656
-I ate everybody's croutons.
-WOMAN: Who let them in?

1011
00:41:13,740 --> 00:41:16,242
Ladies, would you come with us, please?

1012
00:41:16,326 --> 00:41:17,493
We have invites.

1013
00:41:17,577 --> 00:41:19,777
They checked them at
the door and everything.

1014
00:41:27,712 --> 00:41:28,963
He still there?

1015
00:41:29,047 --> 00:41:30,089
-MIDGE: Yep.
-SUSIE: He still big?

1016
00:41:30,173 --> 00:41:31,090
-MIDGE: Yep.
-SUSIE: Mm.

1017
00:41:31,174 --> 00:41:33,176
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

1018
00:41:40,225 --> 00:41:42,560
-Lou.
-Susie Myerson.

1019
00:41:42,644 --> 00:41:45,396
And Mrs. Maisel. It's nice to see you.

1020
00:41:45,480 --> 00:41:47,690
-What is this, Lou?
-LOU: I want you to meet my associate,

1021
00:41:47,774 --> 00:41:49,108
Ken Bruni.

1022
00:41:49,192 --> 00:41:51,527
Ken is Shy's new agent over at MCA.

1023
00:41:51,611 --> 00:41:53,988
Very nice to meet you, ladies.
Enjoying the party?

1024
00:41:54,072 --> 00:41:56,574
-Up until our abduction, it was great.
-LOU: [CHUCKLES] Well,

1025
00:41:56,658 --> 00:41:57,700
we just wanted to say hello

1026
00:41:57,784 --> 00:42:00,411
and fill you in on some exciting news.

1027
00:42:00,495 --> 00:42:03,164
Shy's going to be the lead
in Billy Wilder's next film.

1028
00:42:03,248 --> 00:42:04,582
Did you know he could act?

1029
00:42:04,666 --> 00:42:06,250
I thought today's
performance was pretty good.

1030
00:42:06,334 --> 00:42:07,877
LOU: I'll cut to the chase.

1031
00:42:07,961 --> 00:42:09,420
Everyone here

1032
00:42:09,504 --> 00:42:12,173
is aware of Shy's proclivities.

1033
00:42:12,257 --> 00:42:15,718
But from now on, we're gonna help him

1034
00:42:15,802 --> 00:42:17,011
to stay on the straight and narrow.

1035
00:42:17,095 --> 00:42:19,263
Watch over him 24 hours a day.

1036
00:42:19,347 --> 00:42:21,724
-Isn't that what Reggie does?
-LOU: Reggie's gone.

1037
00:42:21,808 --> 00:42:22,850
Gone?

1038
00:42:22,934 --> 00:42:24,435
-Holy shit.
-LOU: Look,

1039
00:42:24,519 --> 00:42:26,896
he's a good guy, Reggie. I like him.

1040
00:42:26,980 --> 00:42:28,856
But he's too close with Shy

1041
00:42:28,940 --> 00:42:31,150
to control him. There's too much history.

1042
00:42:31,234 --> 00:42:33,110
And too much history
with the band, too, huh?

1043
00:42:33,194 --> 00:42:33,861
KEN: Exactly.

1044
00:42:33,945 --> 00:42:35,321
Shy fought it, but eventually he realized

1045
00:42:35,405 --> 00:42:37,031
it was time to chart a new course.

1046
00:42:37,115 --> 00:42:39,575
All this because I cracked
a couple Judy Garland jokes

1047
00:42:39,659 --> 00:42:41,160
-at the Apollo?
-LOU: No,

1048
00:42:41,244 --> 00:42:42,995
no, this has been a long time coming.

1049
00:42:43,079 --> 00:42:45,331
That night at the Apollo
just gave us an opening.

1050
00:42:45,415 --> 00:42:46,624
So, thank you.

1051
00:42:46,708 --> 00:42:48,626
Reggie got Shy to where he is now.

1052
00:42:48,710 --> 00:42:51,212
-You realize that?
-LOU: Reggie's taken care of.

1053
00:42:51,296 --> 00:42:53,422
Big severance.
We threw him some publishing.

1054
00:42:53,506 --> 00:42:55,216
He's buying a house in Westchester.

1055
00:42:55,300 --> 00:42:57,343
-Everybody's happy.
-SUSIE: Oh, I bet.

1056
00:42:57,427 --> 00:42:58,928
'Cause when you think
Reggie, you think Westchester.

1057
00:42:59,012 --> 00:43:01,013
All right, Lou. Suit guy.

1058
00:43:01,097 --> 00:43:03,182
-Ken.
-Thanks for filling us in

1059
00:43:03,266 --> 00:43:04,642
on a bunch of stuff we
didn't give a fuck about.

1060
00:43:04,726 --> 00:43:05,726
Okay for us to go?

1061
00:43:05,810 --> 00:43:07,436
KEN: Just another minute of your time.

1062
00:43:07,520 --> 00:43:10,231
We understand you and
Shy got pretty friendly on tour

1063
00:43:10,315 --> 00:43:12,233
and that maybe you saw some things.

1064
00:43:12,317 --> 00:43:14,944
One thing in particular
that occurred on a boat.

1065
00:43:15,028 --> 00:43:17,655
We know that you thought
you were helping him,

1066
00:43:17,739 --> 00:43:19,490
so the way it ended up with
you on the tarmac that night,

1067
00:43:19,574 --> 00:43:22,243
it doesn't seem right.
We want to make it right.

1068
00:43:22,327 --> 00:43:23,786
Okay.

1069
00:43:23,870 --> 00:43:25,746
How does $2,000 sound?

1070
00:43:25,830 --> 00:43:27,623
Two thousand dollars? Wow.

1071
00:43:27,707 --> 00:43:30,376
-You want to give me $2,000?
-KEN: In exchange

1072
00:43:30,460 --> 00:43:32,086
for your signature on a legal agreement

1073
00:43:32,170 --> 00:43:34,630
stating that you won't disparage
or besmirch Shy Baldwin

1074
00:43:34,714 --> 00:43:36,966
in any way, publicly or privately.

1075
00:43:37,050 --> 00:43:39,093
You invited me so you could bribe me?

1076
00:43:39,177 --> 00:43:40,678
KEN: It's not a bribe. It's an agreement.

1077
00:43:40,762 --> 00:43:42,972
There is no way I would
ever take $2,000 from you.

1078
00:43:43,056 --> 00:43:45,808
Uh, yeah, right.
Fuck you and your $2,000.

1079
00:43:45,892 --> 00:43:48,269
-How about three?
-Miriam?

1080
00:43:48,353 --> 00:43:51,230
-Nope. Three? Forget it.
-KEN: Five.

1081
00:43:51,314 --> 00:43:53,357
Now, this is getting very interesting.

1082
00:43:53,441 --> 00:43:55,651
-Keep it.
-Yep.

1083
00:43:55,735 --> 00:43:58,654
We thought about it.
Not fucking interested.

1084
00:43:58,738 --> 00:44:00,823
-Ten.
-Okay, Miriam, that's a car.

1085
00:44:00,907 --> 00:44:03,409
Three cars or one big, fancy German car.

1086
00:44:03,493 --> 00:44:05,704
-A shiny, Nazi Mercedes.
-No.

1087
00:44:05,788 --> 00:44:07,664
-No.
-Fuck! No.

1088
00:44:07,748 --> 00:44:09,249
Last and best. Twelve.

1089
00:44:09,333 --> 00:44:11,293
Oh, are there harps playing somewhere?

1090
00:44:11,377 --> 00:44:13,003
-I'm hearing harps.
-We're done here.

1091
00:44:13,087 --> 00:44:14,129
-We are?
-Yes.

1092
00:44:14,213 --> 00:44:15,297
-Come on.
-KEN: We'd like you

1093
00:44:15,381 --> 00:44:16,506
to reconsider. The offer's gone

1094
00:44:16,590 --> 00:44:17,674
as soon as you walk out the door.

1095
00:44:17,758 --> 00:44:19,259
I promised Shy I would never tell anyone

1096
00:44:19,343 --> 00:44:20,385
about that night, and I haven't.

1097
00:44:20,469 --> 00:44:22,262
I promised Shy.

1098
00:44:22,346 --> 00:44:24,264
SUSIE: Let's go.

1099
00:44:24,348 --> 00:44:26,016
-Unless you want to…
-I want nothing from them.

1100
00:44:26,100 --> 00:44:28,852
Yep, me, neither. Let's go. Fuck you.

1101
00:44:28,936 --> 00:44:30,437
Stupid idea to come here.

1102
00:44:30,521 --> 00:44:32,856
-Was that aimed at me?
-No. Yes.

1103
00:44:32,940 --> 00:44:35,525
-This was your idea.
-My idea? If it wasn't for you,

1104
00:44:35,609 --> 00:44:36,818
I wouldn't have found
my invite to this thing

1105
00:44:36,902 --> 00:44:38,987
for, like, ten months,
so this is your fault.

1106
00:44:39,071 --> 00:44:40,572
Fuck it. We're getting gift bags.

1107
00:44:40,656 --> 00:44:43,116
That's tacky.
I bet there's not even anything good…

1108
00:44:43,200 --> 00:44:44,826
Oh, my God, it's Chanel No. 5.

1109
00:44:44,910 --> 00:44:47,037
-Get one for Grandma Mary.
-Who?

1110
00:44:47,121 --> 00:44:49,289
Our grandmother who couldn't come tonight

1111
00:44:49,373 --> 00:44:51,708
but was also invited
and loves Chanel No. 5.

1112
00:44:51,792 --> 00:44:54,211
-Got it.
-I'll meet you outside.

1113
00:45:13,105 --> 00:45:15,357
-Where the hell were you?
-I was looking for a cab.

1114
00:45:15,441 --> 00:45:17,192
You told me, "Meet me out front."

1115
00:45:17,276 --> 00:45:18,735
There weren't any cabs
out front, so I thought

1116
00:45:18,819 --> 00:45:20,028
I'd go around the corner
because I remembered

1117
00:45:20,112 --> 00:45:21,196
that whenever I shop at Bergdorf's,

1118
00:45:21,280 --> 00:45:22,781
I always go out the
side door to grab a cab

1119
00:45:22,865 --> 00:45:25,033
-before they turn onto Fifth.
-I got this cab on Fifth.

1120
00:45:25,117 --> 00:45:26,743
Well, it's not a foolproof plan.

1121
00:45:26,827 --> 00:45:28,328
Just get in the goddamn car.

1122
00:45:28,412 --> 00:45:29,997
Next time, I leave you here.

1123
00:45:40,299 --> 00:45:42,217
[SIGHS]

1124
00:45:50,934 --> 00:45:52,769
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

1125
00:45:52,853 --> 00:45:56,314
<i>♪ Baby… ♪</i>
-The till's over.

1126
00:45:56,398 --> 00:45:57,524
Over?

1127
00:45:57,608 --> 00:45:59,526
That's not possible.
I did the count myself.

1128
00:45:59,610 --> 00:46:01,111
I counted twice. There's an extra five.

1129
00:46:01,195 --> 00:46:02,821
Give it. I must've screwed up.

1130
00:46:02,905 --> 00:46:04,531
-Thanks for catching it.
-[CASH REGISTER DINGS]

1131
00:46:04,615 --> 00:46:07,659
-You know this guy?
-Pop. What are you doing here?

1132
00:46:07,743 --> 00:46:09,077
I was in the area

1133
00:46:09,161 --> 00:46:10,954
seeing one of my notions
and trimmings guys

1134
00:46:11,038 --> 00:46:12,122
and thought I'd stop by.

1135
00:46:12,206 --> 00:46:13,623
Well, come on in. I'll spot you a drink.

1136
00:46:13,707 --> 00:46:15,125
Place looks good.

1137
00:46:15,209 --> 00:46:18,837
The decor, the ambience. Very impressive.

1138
00:46:18,921 --> 00:46:21,089
Last time I was here, it
was covered in buttons.

1139
00:46:21,173 --> 00:46:23,633
-Couple of whiskies for me and my pop.
-You got it, boss.

1140
00:46:23,717 --> 00:46:25,510
"Boss." I like the sound of that.

1141
00:46:25,594 --> 00:46:28,138
-It does not get old.
-You know that the key

1142
00:46:28,222 --> 00:46:31,099
to a great relationship with
your employees is respect.

1143
00:46:31,183 --> 00:46:32,851
In order for them to be productive,

1144
00:46:32,935 --> 00:46:34,561
they got to think you
trust them unconditionally.

1145
00:46:34,645 --> 00:46:36,438
-Absolutely.
-But every one of them's a thief,

1146
00:46:36,522 --> 00:46:38,273
-so don't trust a single one.
-I know.

1147
00:46:38,357 --> 00:46:40,650
I put an extra five in the
till, and he called it out.

1148
00:46:40,734 --> 00:46:43,111
And didn't pocket it.
That means he's a keeper.

1149
00:46:43,195 --> 00:46:45,405
-I was taught by the best.
-[CHUCKLES]

1150
00:46:45,489 --> 00:46:46,823
Thanks.

1151
00:46:46,907 --> 00:46:48,575
Any chance your girlfriend's around?

1152
00:46:48,659 --> 00:46:51,244
No. It's crunch time at school for her.

1153
00:46:51,328 --> 00:46:53,705
-Always with the books.
-In the summer?

1154
00:46:53,789 --> 00:46:55,874
-It's medical school.
-Medical school.

1155
00:46:55,958 --> 00:46:57,167
Well, well, well.

1156
00:46:57,251 --> 00:46:59,169
She sounds interesting, this girl.

1157
00:46:59,253 --> 00:47:01,004
She is. She's great.

1158
00:47:01,088 --> 00:47:04,007
With a lot of different sides to her.
Conflicting sides.

1159
00:47:04,091 --> 00:47:06,176
-What?
-Well, the other night,

1160
00:47:06,260 --> 00:47:07,595
the first half of dinner, she was Rachel,

1161
00:47:07,679 --> 00:47:09,305
sometime before kugel, she was Rebecca,

1162
00:47:09,389 --> 00:47:11,265
after kugel she was Ruth.
You kept them biblical.

1163
00:47:11,349 --> 00:47:13,184
-That was nice.
-I was nervous.

1164
00:47:13,268 --> 00:47:15,421
And I corrected myself.
You remember that, right?

1165
00:47:15,505 --> 00:47:15,729
I do.

1166
00:47:15,813 --> 00:47:17,271
Just trying to think
when was the last time

1167
00:47:17,355 --> 00:47:19,148
I called Shirley Sheila or Trudy.

1168
00:47:19,232 --> 00:47:21,150
Or had to think for a couple of seconds

1169
00:47:21,234 --> 00:47:22,735
when somebody asked how we met.

1170
00:47:22,819 --> 00:47:24,862
Ma's questions come
pretty fast and furious, Pop.

1171
00:47:24,946 --> 00:47:26,572
-You know that.
-Mm-hmm.

1172
00:47:26,656 --> 00:47:28,616
Listen, so you know,

1173
00:47:28,700 --> 00:47:30,910
what I know is all I need to know.

1174
00:47:30,994 --> 00:47:33,621
-I don't know.
-You like her.

1175
00:47:33,705 --> 00:47:35,748
That's all I know.
That's all I need to know.

1176
00:47:35,832 --> 00:47:39,335
But keep in mind your
mother is very excited

1177
00:47:39,419 --> 00:47:40,753
about Rachel Rebecca Ruth,

1178
00:47:40,837 --> 00:47:42,630
and when she gets excited about something

1179
00:47:42,714 --> 00:47:44,215
and that something disappoints her,

1180
00:47:44,299 --> 00:47:46,175
our house gets very small and loud.

1181
00:47:46,259 --> 00:47:48,010
-I get it.
-The good news is

1182
00:47:48,094 --> 00:47:50,346
your dinner appearance
got you a little reprieve

1183
00:47:50,430 --> 00:47:51,472
from her trying to set you up

1184
00:47:51,556 --> 00:47:53,474
with every single Jewish girl she sees,

1185
00:47:53,558 --> 00:47:55,184
including your cousin Rachel.

1186
00:47:55,268 --> 00:47:57,061
You can start answering your phone again.

1187
00:47:57,145 --> 00:47:58,479
Great.

1188
00:47:58,563 --> 00:48:00,773
So, there really is a girl?

1189
00:48:00,857 --> 00:48:02,900
-Yes. There really is.
-Okay.

1190
00:48:02,984 --> 00:48:05,069
That's all I need to know. For now.

1191
00:48:05,153 --> 00:48:07,238
You got to open. I'll see you around.

1192
00:48:07,322 --> 00:48:09,198
-Thank you.
-How many are you?

1193
